                <h1>Effortless Ways to Remove Wallpaper from Plaster Walls</h1>
                <p>Removing wallpaper from plaster walls can be challenging but achievable with the right technique. Start by scoring the wallpaper with a utility knife and applying a wallpaper removal solution to loosen the adhesive. Use a scraper to gently peel away the layers, taking care not to damage the plaster underneath. Clean any residue afterward for a smooth surface.</p>
